# Cursor / AI assistant rules — WiamApp

This repo is **WiamApp** only. It is one of several separate WiamLabs
products, each in its own repository with its own stack. Do not assume
conventions, dependencies, or file structures from any other WiamLabs
product (WiamPass, WiamTrade, wiamlabs-web, wiamlabs-studio) apply here
— they do not, even where names sound similar.

## Stack (this repo only)
- Backend: **Express** (plain, not NestJS), ES modules (`type: module`)
- Database: **Supabase** (PostgreSQL) accessed via `@supabase/supabase-js`
  — no ORM, no Prisma
- Mobile: **Expo / React Native**, built via EAS
- Web: **Next.js 15/16** (App Router), two separate apps: `marketing/`
  (public site) and `business-web/` (portal, proxied under
  `wiamapp.com/business/*` — see `marketing/next.config.js` rewrites)
- Package manager: **npm** (not pnpm, not yarn)
- Payments: Paystack, routed through the separate
  `wiamlabs-payments-router` service — this repo's own webhook code
  never needs to change when other products are added to that router

## Structure
```
backend/         Express API — own package.json, own node_modules
mobile/          Expo app — own package.json
marketing/       Next.js — own package.json
business-web/    Next.js — own package.json, proxied under marketing
database/        Supabase SQL migrations, run manually, not via ORM
docs/            MASTER_PLAN.md — full product spec, read before large changes
```
Four independent Node projects live in this one repo. Never assume a
dependency in one is available in another — install separately per folder.

## Before making changes
Read `docs/MASTER_PLAN.md` for anything touching booking flow, trust
system, verification, payments, or the screen/route list — it is the
authoritative spec and is kept current (see its Section 29 for the
latest architecture changes).

## Hard rules
- Never suggest switching this repo to Prisma, NestJS, or pnpm — those
  belong to WiamPass, a different product, different repo.
- Never invent a `wiamapp.team.wiamlabs.com` or similar admin panel —
  WiamLabs is building a separate cross-product Studio for that
  (see `wiamlabs-studio` repo). Do not build WiamApp-specific admin UI.
- `wiamapp.com/business/*` is a rewrite proxy to a separate deployed
  service (`business-web`), not a folder inside `marketing/`. Do not
  "fix" this by merging the two Next.js apps.
